VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT (?i)\bSELECT\b.*\bORDER BY\b.*\s@\w+
WHEN EXPR PRESENT:(?i)\b(exec|sp_executesql|query|command)\b
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects the usage of SELECT statements with ORDER BY clauses and a specified input name.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for SQL Query: SELECT Statement with ORDER BY and @InputName.
